          "date": "2024-01-11 18:00:14.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-17322 yalt: Yet Another Lustre Tester",
        "message": "LU-17322 yalt: Yet Another Lustre Tester\n\nNew testing script written in Python designed to\nenable new features to the Lustre test framework\nwithout breaking compatibility with current testing\ntools.\n\nThis patch contains a first revision of this tool.\nIt intends to replicate the functionality of the\ncurrent Lustre testing tools, while setting up\nsome infrastructure for later patches.\n\nThis tool allows for custom test providers to\nbe defined. The job of a provider is to setup\nthe environment and infrastructure needed\nto run Lustre sanity tests. The providers are\ndefined a separate scripts with a common API.\nThis mean that they can be written in any\nlanguage and make use of any IaC tools.\n\nTODO:\n- Add simple QEMU testing provider\n- Add 'env' command which explains common\n  environment variables and does a sanity\n  check on the current environment\n- Improve documentation\n\nTest-Parameters: forbuildonly\nSigned-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@amazon.com>\nChange-Id: I262317e2c05d3a2f845eacfc1ac64f9d83608e2b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
